A Tongaat taxi owner (35) was shot and killed on Thursday morning while he was sitting in his parked vehicle. Police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala, said the murder is being investigated by Tongaat police. Gwala said the 35-year-old taxi owner was shot by two unknown people at Maidstone Village at about 10.30 am on Thursday. “He sustained multiple gunshot wounds to the body and was certified dead at the scene.” According to Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) spokesperson, Prem Balram, a patrolling Rusa officer was flagged down by a witness who reported the shooting. “According to the man, two suspects walked up to a blue Hyundai Getz and shot the driver multiple times through his window before they fled in a white unknown vehicle,” said Balram. Paramedics from a private ambulance service declared the man dead and several spent cartridges were recovered at the scene. The motive for the murder is unknown at this stage. No arrests have been made.